@anchor{Function ensure-symbol}
@deffn {Function} {ensure-symbol} name @&optional package
@findex ensure-symbol
Returns a symbol with name designated by @code{name}, accessible in package
designated by @code{package}. If symbol is not already accessible in @code{package}, it is
interned there. Returns a secondary value reflecting the status of the symbol
in the package, which matches the secondary return value of @code{intern}.

Example:

@lisp
  (ensure-symbol :cons :cl) => cl:cons, :external
@end lisp
@end deffn
